layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 15 20; written lines: 15 20; Uniform layout. Visible pencil ruling.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Ashkenazi semi-cursive (punctuated) and Latin scripts of the 16th century.

binding.p: Post-1600. Brown leather, blind tooled. Spine: 'Lexicon Hebr. Abr. Mus. Brit. Jure Empt. 19,893.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Purchased by the British Museum through B. Quaritch on 01 July 1854: inscribed, folio [93v] (fse001v).
